{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MZvdwo5isL772tYzBjGp9S","type":"tool_result","content":"   250→  - `txSignature` only included when present (completed claims)\n   251→  - `amountLamports` returned as string (lamports-only accounting)\n   252→  - Error handling: catches and logs failures, returns 500\n   253→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   254→\n   255→## Iteration 13 — 2026-03-25T12:14:13Z — OK\n   256→- **Log**: iteration-013.log\n   257→\n   258→## Iteration 14 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   259→\n   260→**Item**: [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n   261→**Status**: Done\n   262→**Changes**:\n   263→- Added `import { createReferralRoutes } from \"./routes/referral.js\"` to `services/backend/src/index.ts`\n   264→- Added JWT auth middleware for `/referral/*` with `requireAllMethods: true` (ensures auth on GET + POST)\n   265→- Mounted routes with `app.route(\"/referral\", createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config }))` after profile routes\n   266→- Passes all 3 deps required by `ReferralRoutesDeps`: `db` (from createDb), `sql` (raw postgres connection), `config` (from loadConfig)\n   267→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   268→\n   269→## Iteration 14 — 2026-03-25T12:17:10Z — OK\n   270→- **Log**: iteration-014.log\n   271→\n   272→## Iteration 15 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   273→\n   274→**Item**: [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: referral earnings recording after game settlement\n   275→**Status**: Done\n   276→**Changes**:\n   277→- Added `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to `SettleTxDeps` interface\n   278→- Added `recordReferralEarnings()` helper function in `settle-tx.ts`:\n   279→  - Takes roundId, gameType, feeBps, referralDefaultRateBps, and player list\n   280→  - Deduplicates players (handles Lord of RNGs multiple entries per player)\n   281→  - For each player: checks `getReferralLinkByReferee()` → if referrer exists, gets rate via `getReferrerRate()` (KOL override)\n   282→  - Calculates `referrerEarned = feeLamports * referrerRateBps / 10000` and `refereeRebate = feeLamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%)\n   283→  - Inserts via `db.insertReferralEarning()` with all economic inputs preserved\n   284→  - Error handling: duplicate key (idempotent skip), other errors logged but don't fail settlement\n   285→- Called `recordReferralEarnings()` at end of `settleMatch()` (coinflip — 2 players) and `settleLordRound()` (lord — N players)\n   286→- Updated caller in `index.ts` to pass `referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps`\n   287→- Updated integration test to pass `referralDefaultRateBps: 1000` in SettleTxDeps\n   288→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   289→\n   290→## Iteration 15 — 2026-03-25T12:25:43Z — OK\n   291→- **Log**: iteration-015.log\n   292→\n   293→## Iteration 16 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   294→\n   295→**Item**: [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity\n   296→**Status**: Done\n   297→**Changes**:\n   298→- Added `withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>` method to `Db` interface in `db.ts`\n   299→- Refactored `createDb()` to accept an optional `_txSql` parameter for transaction injection. When provided, the sql object is used directly (no new connection). `close()` is guarded to only close owned connections.\n   300→- `withTransaction` implementation uses `sql.begin()` to create a transaction scope and passes a transactional `Db` (via recursive `createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)`) to the callback\n   301→- In `settle-tx.ts` `settleMatch()`: wrapped all post-confirmation DB writes (updateRoundPhase, updateRoundEntries, insertOperatorEvent, insertTransaction, recordReferralEarnings) in `db.withTransaction()`\n   302→- In `settle-tx.ts` `settleLordRound()`: same wrapping for Lord of RNGs settlement writes\n   303→- All writes within the transaction use `txDb` instead of `db`, ensuring they share the same transaction connection\n   304→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   305→\n   306→## Iteration 16 — 2026-03-25T12:37:33Z — OK\n   307→- **Log**: iteration-016.log\n   308→\n   309→## Iteration 17 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   310→\n   311→**Item**: [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry\n   312→**Status**: Done\n   313→**Changes**:\n   314→- Created `services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` with `createClaimHandler()` factory\n   315→  - Accepts `ClaimHandlerDeps`: db, connection, serverKeypair\n   316→  - Returns an `EventHandler` function for the queue worker\n   317→  - Idempotent: skips if claim status is already `completed` or `failed`\n   318→  - Flow: load claim → update to `processing` → re-verify pending balance >= claim amount → build SystemProgram.transfer tx → send + confirm → update to `completed` with tx_signature\n   319→  - On insufficient balance: updates to `failed` with descriptive error (no re-throw, terminal)\n   320→  - On transfer failure: updates to `failed` + re-throws so queue worker retries with exponential backoff\n   321→  - Uses web3.js v1 patterns consistent with settle-tx.ts (Transaction, sign, sendRawTransaction, confirmTransaction)\n   322→- Updated `services/backend/src/index.ts`:\n   323→  - Imported `registerHandler`, `EventTypes` from queue, and `createClaimHandler` from handler\n   324→  - Registered handler before event worker starts: `registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED, createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair }))`\n   325→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   326→\n   327→## Iteration 17 — 2026-03-25T12:47:48Z — OK\n   328→- **Log**: iteration-017.log\n   329→\n   330→## Iteration 18 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   331→\n   332→**Item**: [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` — 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth\n   333→**Status**: Done\n   334→**Changes**:\n   335→- Created `apps/platform/src/lib/referral-api.ts` following `auth-api.ts` pattern\n   336→- Response type interfaces: `ReferralCodeResponse`, `ApplyReferralResponse`, `ReferralStatsResponse`, `ReferralEarningItem`, `ReferralEarningsResponse`, `ClaimResponse`\n   337→- Shared `parseResponse<T>()` utility with error extraction from `{ error: { message } }` shape\n   338→- `authHeaders(token)` helper for `Authorization: Bearer` + `Content-Type: application/json`\n   339→- 7 exported async functions: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings` (with optional page/limit query params), `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`\n   340→- All monetary values typed as `string` (lamports-only accounting)\n   341→- Fixed lint error: replaced `URLSearchParams` (not in ESLint globals) with manual query string construction\n   342→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18)\n   343→\n   344→## Iteration 18 — 2026-03-25T12:52:39Z — OK\n   345→- **Log**: iteration-018.log\n   346→\n   347→## Iteration 19 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   348→\n   349→**Item**: [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` — capture code to localStorage, redirect to `/`\n   350→**Status**: Done\n   351→**Changes**:\n   352→- Added `Navigate` and `useParams` imports from `react-router-dom` in `App.tsx`\n   353→- Created `ReferralCapture` component:\n   354→  - Reads `:code` from URL params via `useParams()`\n   355→  - Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` as JSON in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   356→  - Gracefully handles