{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lbc3QFfwCsMEC17ctBnBWJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## E2E Test Setup Exploration Report\n\n### 1. **Test Framework & Location**\n\n**Framework**: Playwright 1.58.2 (test runner for browser automation)\n\n**Locations**:\n- Main E2E directory: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/`\n- Sub-directories:\n  - `local/` — Local validator tests (7 test files)\n  - `devnet/` — Devnet tests (5 test files)\n  - `visual/` — Visual regression tests (2 test files)\n  - `real/` — Real/staging tests (1 test file)\n  - `helpers/` — Shared helpers (profile assertions)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Test Directory Structure**\n\n```\ne2e/\n├── fixtures.ts                    # Visual regression fixture (animation freeze, deterministic seeding)\n├── local/\n│   ├── fixtures.ts               # Dual-player browser context fixture (playerA/playerB with injected keypairs)\n│   ├── 00-smoke.spec.ts          # App loads in real wallet mode\n│   ├── 01-error-flow.spec.ts     # Error cases: insufficient balance, join unavailable match, settle already-claimed\n│   ├── 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts    # Create → cancel → refund → recreate flow\n│   ├── 03-lifecycle.spec.ts      # Full lifecycle: create → join → resolve → claim\n│   ├── 10-lord-smoke.spec.ts     # Lord of RNGs page load smoke test\n│   ├── 11-lord-lifecycle.spec.ts # Lord full lifecycle: create → join → countdown → settle\n│   ├── 20-profile-transactions.spec.ts # Play match → verify transaction history\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── wallets.ts            # Deterministic keypairs (PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B)\n│       ├── localnet-setup.ts     # Initialize on-chain configs (not funded)\n│       ├── page-objects.ts       # UI action helpers (create, join, cancel, claim, etc.)\n│       ├── lord-page-objects.ts  # Lord-specific UI helpers\n│       └── on-chain.ts           # RPC assertions (match PDAs, treasury, fee verification)\n├── devnet/\n│   ├── fixtures.ts               # Devnet config fixture (validates env vars)\n│   ├── smoke.spec.ts             # Verify RPC health + deployed programs + wallet connection\n│   ├── lifecycle.spec.ts         # Full lifecycle on devnet with VRF + backend settlement\n│   ├── lord-lifecycle.spec.ts    # Lord lifecycle on devnet\n│   ├── closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts # Close Call lifecycle\n│   ├── deeplink.spec.ts          # Deep-link to match page by ID\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── wallets.ts            # Deterministic keypairs\n│       ├── env.ts                # Validate VITE_RPC_URL, program IDs, backend health\n│       ├── retry.ts              # Retry helper for async operations\n│       ├── on-chain-cleanup.ts   # Clean stale matches before/after tests\n│       ├── vrf-polling.ts        # Poll Orao VRF for fulfillment\n│       ├── mock-vrf-fallback.ts  # Fallback mock VRF if real VRF times out\n│       ├── tx-utils.ts           # Transaction signing utilities\n│       └── [lord-specific helpers]\n├── visual/\n│   ├── routes.spec.ts            # Visual snapshots of key routes (home, coinflip, etc.)\n│   └── states.spec.ts            # Visual snapshots of UI states (winning, losing, loading, etc.)\n└── real/\n    └── startup.spec.ts           # Smoke test for staging/production\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Test Framework Details**\n\n#### **Playwright Configuration Files**\n\n| File | Purpose | Target | Workers | Timeout | Web Server |\n|------|---------|--------|---------|---------|------------|\n| `playwright.config.ts` | Visual regression tests (snapshot-based) | `visual/**` | 1 | 60s | Vite on port 3000 (VITE_MOCK_MODE=true) |\n| `playwright.local.config.ts` | Local E2E tests (real wallet mode against local validator) | `local/**` | 1 | 60s | Vite on port 3002 (VITE_TEST_WALLET=true) |\n| `playwright.devnet.config.ts` | Devnet E2E tests (real programs with VRF) | `devnet/**` | 1 | 300s | Vite on port 3003 (inherits env vars) |\n| `playwright.real.config.ts` | Staging/production tests | `real/**` | 1 | Default | Manual (no web server) |\n\n**Key Configuration Details**:\n- **Parallel execution**: Disabled (workers: 1) — all tests run serially to avoid race conditions\n- **Retries**: 0 for local/visual, 2 for devnet (VRF can be slow)\n- **Screenshots**: Off for local/visual, only-on-failure for devnet, on for devnet video\n- **Trace**: Off for visual, retain-on-failure for local and devnet\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Fixtures**\n\n#### **Visual Regression Fixture** (`e2e/fixtures.ts`)\n\nExtends Playwright's `test` fixture with `stablePage`:\n- **Deterministic randomness**: Seeds Math.random() with Mulberry32 (seed 42)\n- **Crypto seeding**: Injects seeded crypto.getRandomValues() for deterministic Keypair.generate()\n- **Frozen Date**: Date.now() returns fixed timestamp (2026-01-01)\n- **Animation freezing**: Injects CSS to disable all transitions and animations\n- **SVG animation pausing**: Calls pauseAnimations() on all SVG elements\n- **Font readiness**: Waits for document.fonts.ready before proceeding\n- **Console error filtering**: Collects errors, filters noise (401, 403, 429, favicon, backend not running), fails if unhandled errors exist\n\n**Usage**:\n```ts\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\ntest(\"example\", async ({ stablePage }) => { ... });\n```\n\n#### **Local E2E Dual-Player Fixture** (`e2e/local/fixtures.ts`)\n\nExtends Playwright's `test` fixture with:\n- **playerAContext / playerBContext**: Isolated browser contexts for two players\n- **playerAPage / playerBPage**: Pages within each context\n- **playerAKeypair / playerBKeypair**: Deterministic keypairs (same as PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B from wallets.ts)\n- **connection**: Shared Solana RPC connection to local validator\n\n**Key mechanism**: Each context gets a `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` injected via `addInitScript()`, allowing TestWalletProvider to construct the correct Keypair at React render time.\n\n**Usage**:\n```ts\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\ntest(\"lifecycle\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, connection }) => { ... });\n```\n\n#### **Devnet Fixture** (`e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts`)\n\nSimilar to local fixture but also exposes:\n- **devnetConfig**: Validated config object with RPC URL, program IDs, backend URL\n- **connection**: Connection to devnet RPC (not local)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Test Framework: What's Tested**\n\n#### **Local E2E Tests** (against local validator)\n\n1. **00-smoke.spec.ts**: App loads, header visible, wallet button visible, no console errors\n2. **01-error-flow.spec.ts**: \n   - Insufficient balance → creation rejected, no PDA created\n   - Join unavailable (cancelled) match → stays in lobby\n   - Settle already-claimed match → no stale settle buttons\n3. **02-cancel-flow.spec.ts**: \n   - Create → cancel → refund flow\n   - Balance validation (rent cost < 0.01 SOL)\n   - Re-creation after cancel\n4. **03-lifecycle.spec.ts** (Full lifecycle):\n   - Player A creates match (iron tier, heads)\n   - Player B joins match\n   - Backend settles (pre-loaded mock VRF in local validator)\n   - Match PDA closes, treasury fee deducted\n   - Winner can return to lobby\n   - Console error tracking\n5. **10-lord-smoke.spec.ts**: Lord of RNGs page loads\n6. **11-lord-lifecycle.spec.ts**:\n   - Create round → Player B joins (countdown starts) → backend settlement → verify treasury fee\n   - Uses withRetry() helper to poll round state\n7. **20-profile-transactions.spec.ts**:\n   - Play coinflip match → navigate to profile → click Transactions tab\n   - Verify transaction history (DEPOSIT, PAYOUT) displays in SOL\n   - Verify deep-links to `/coinflip/:matchId`\n\n#### **Devnet E2E Tests** (against deployed programs with real VRF)\n\n1. **smoke.spec.ts**:\n   - Verify devnet deployments reachable (RPC health, programs deployed)\n   - App loads against devnet\n   - Wallet connects with test keypair\n2. **lifecycle.spec.ts**:\n   - Create → join → backend settle (with VRF fulfillment) → verify\n   - Settlement timeout: 120s (VRF can take up to 180s)\n   - Uses withRetry() to poll round settlement\n3. **lord-lifecycle.spec.ts**: Similar to local, but with real VRF fulfillment\n4. **closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts**: Close Call (BTC prediction) game lifecycle\n5. **deeplink.spec.ts**: Navigate directly to `/coinflip/:matchId` and verify match loads\n\n#### **Visual Tests** (snapshot-based)\n\n1. **routes.spec.ts**: Snapshots of key routes (/, /coinflip, /lord-of-rngs, /profile)\n2. **states.spec.ts**: Snapshots of specific UI states (winning state, losing state, loading, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Helper Functions Overview**\n\n#### **Page Objects** (`local/helpers/page-objects.ts`, 426 lines)\n\n**Selectors** (CSS class-based):\n- Lobby: `.coinflip-lobby`, sidebar, main area\n- Tier selector: `.rng-tier-selector`, `.rng-tier-btn`, `.rng-tier-gem--{tier}`\n- Side selector: `.coinflip-side-btn--heads/tails`\n- Match cards: `.coinflip-match-card`, `.coinflip-match-card__join-btn`\n- Active match: `.coinflip-active-match`, `.coinflip-active-match__waiting`, `.coinflip-active-match__playing`\n- Result: `.coinflip-result__outcome`, `.coinflip-result__payout`\n- Error: `.rng-toast--error`\n\n**Key Actions**:\n- `waitForWalletConnected(page, timeout)` — wait for `.rng-wallet-button--connected`\n- `navigateToCoinflip(page)` — goto `/coinflip`, wait for main area\n- `enterWager(page, amountSol)` — fill `.rng-wager-input__input`\n- `selectSide(page, \"heads\"|\"tails\")` — click side button\n- `createMatch(page, amountSol, side)` — enter wager, select side, click \"Create Game\"\n- `joinMatch(page, matchIndex)` — click join button on nth match card\n- `cancelMatch(page)` — click \"Cancel Match\"\n- `claimOrSettle(page)` — click \"Claim Payout\" / \"Settle & Return\"\n- `backToLobby(page)` — click \"Back to Lobby\"\n- `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)` — wait for `.coinflip-sidebar__status` text\n- `waitForResult(page, timeout)` — poll UI for result (won/lost)\n- `assertLobbyEmpty(page)` — verify no match cards\n- `trackConsoleErrors(page)` — collect console errors (filters noise)\n\n#### **On-Chain Helpers** (`local/helpers/on-chain.ts`, 415 lines)\n\n**RPC Query Helpers**:\n- `getCoinflipProgram(connection)` — create Anchor program instance\n- `getMatchPda(creator, matchId)` — derive match PDA from [\"match\", creator, matchId]\n- `getConfigPda()` — derive coinflip config PDA\n- `snapshotBalance(connection, pubkey)` — get balance in lamports\n- `getBalanceLamports(connection, pubkey)` — same as snapshot\n\n**Assertion Helpers**:\n- `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, side)` — fetch match PDA, verify phase=0 (waiting), return { matchPda, creator, opponent (PublicKey.default), entryAmount }\n- `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)` — verify account no longer exists or phase=settled/refunded\n- `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` — verify fee deducted: expected = Math.floor((entryAmount * 500) / 10000), actual = balanceAfter - balanceBefore, within ±10 lamports\n\n**Match Account Shape**:\n```ts\ninterface MatchAccount {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number; // 0=waiting, 1=locked, 2=settled, 3=refunded\n  commitment: Uint8Array;\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  targetSlot: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  resultHash: Uint8Array;\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  matchId: number[];\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n#### **Wallets** (`local/helpers/wallets.ts`, 87 lines)\n\n**Fixed Keypairs**:\n- `PLAYER_A` = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa))\n- `PLAYER_B` = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb))\n- Same keypairs used on every test run (deterministic)\n\n**Airdrop Helpers**:\n- `fundWallet(connection, pubkey, solAmount)` — request airdrop, confirm\n- `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl, solAmount)` — fund both players, verify balances, return { playerA, playerB, connection }\n\n#### **Localnet Setup** (`local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`, 197 lines)\n\n**Initialization**:\n- `initializeLocalnet()` — create platform config, coinflip config on local validator\n- `ensurePlayerProfiles()` — create player profile PDAs for testing profile transactions\n\n#### **Lord of RNGs Helpers** (`local/helpers/lord-page-objects.ts`, 308 lines)\n\n**Actions**:\n- `navigateToLord(page)` — goto `/lord-of-rngs`\n- `joinRound(page)` — click join button\n- `selectTier(page, tierIndex)` — select tier by index\n- `waitForSettlementUi(page, timeout)` — wait for settlement state in UI\n- Similar pattern to coinflip page objects\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Test Runner Scripts**\n\n#### **Local E2E Runner** (`scripts/run-e2e-local.sh`, 151 lines)\n\n**Full flow**:\n1. Start solana-test-validator with programs preloaded\n2. Check/start PostgreSQL\n3. Generate backend signer keypair\n4. Fund backend signer with 2 SOL\n5. Run backend migrations (DATABASE_URL, DB_SCHEMA, RPC_URL)\n6. Start fairness backend on port 3101 (or custom PORT)\n7. Wait for backend health check\n8. Run Playwright tests: `playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts`\n9. Cleanup on exit (kill backend, teardown validator)\n\n**Environment variables**:\n- `RPC_URL` (default: http://127.0.0.1:8899)\n- `PORT` (default: 3101)\n- `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (passed to web server)\n- `DATABASE_URL` (postgres:///postgres)\n- `DB_SCHEMA` (local_e2e)\n\n**Entry command**: `npm run test:e2e:local` or `pnpm test:e2e:local`\n\n#### **Devnet E2E Runner** (`scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh`, 170 lines)\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Source .env.local or .env.devnet for VITE_* vars\n2. Source backend .env for DATABASE_URL, SERVER_KEYPAIR, RPC_URL\n3. Validate required env vars (VITE_RPC_URL, VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID)\n4. Check if backend is already running (curl /health)\n5. If not: run migrations and start backend on port 3100\n6. Run Playwright tests: `playwright test --config playwright.devnet.config.ts`\n7. Cleanup on exit\n\n**Required env vars**:\n- `VITE_RPC_URL` — devnet RPC endpoint (default: dRPC)\n- `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`\n- `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID`\n- `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (default: http://127.0.0.1:3100)\n\n**Entry command**: `npm run test:e2e:devnet` or `pnpm test:e2e:devnet`\n\n#### **Localnet Bootstrap** (`scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh`, 125 lines)\n\n**Starts solana-test-validator**:\n- Preloads 3 programs at fixed IDs: coinflip, platform, lordofrngs\n- Preloads Orao mock VRF accounts (network state, treasury, randomness for players)\n- Ledger dir: `.localnet-ledger`\n- Waits for RPC health, max 30s\n- Writes validator PID to `.localnet.pid`\n\n**Teardown** (`scripts/localnet-teardown.sh`):\n- Kills validator process by PID\n- Removes ledger directory\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Test Execution Order & Mode**\n\n**Local tests**:\n- **Serial**: 01-error-flow (serial block inside), 20-profile-transactions (serial block inside)\n- **Parallel-capable but run serially**: 00-smoke, 02-cancel, 03-lifecycle, 10-lord-smoke, 11-lord-lifecycle\n- **Execution**: Single worker, no parallelism across files\n\n**Devnet tests**:\n- **Serial**: All tests run serially (workers: 1)\n- **Retries**: 2 (to handle VRF timing variations)\n- **Long timeout**: 300s (VRF fulfillment can take up to 180s)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Page Objects & Selectors Summary**\n\n**Coinflip Page Structure**:\n- `.coinflip-page` (root container)\n  - `.coinflip-sidebar` (left: tier, side, summary, action button)\n  - `.coinflip-main` (right: lobby or active match)\n    - `.coinflip-lobby` (open matches list)\n      - `.coinflip-matches__list` → `.coinflip-match-card` (each match)\n    - `.coinflip-active-match` (in-progress or settled match)\n      - `.coinflip-active-match__waiting` (awaiting opponent)\n      - `.coinflip-active-match__playing` (countdown/revealing)\n      - `.coinflip-result__outcome` (won/lost)\n      - `.coinflip-result__payout` (amount)\n      - `.coinflip-active-match__post-claim` (after claiming)\n\n**Lord of RNGs Page Structure**:\n- Similar pattern: sidebar (tier select) + main (round list / active round)\n\n**Profile Page Structure**:\n- `.profile-page__header`\n- `button:has-text(\"Transactions\")` (tab selector)\n- `.profile-transactions__table` (transaction history)\n- `.profile-transactions__table tbody tr` (rows)\n- `.profile-transactions__match-link` (deep-link to /coinflip/:matchId)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Test Patterns**\n\n1. **Dual-player tests**: Use playerAPage + playerBPage from fixture, both auto-connect with test wallet\n2. **On-chain assertions**: After UI actions, query RPC to verify PDA state (phase, amount, winner)\n3. **Console error tracking**: Every test calls `trackConsoleErrors(page).assertClean()` at end\n4. **Retry with backoff**: Use `withRetry()` helper for eventual consistency (settlement can take time)\n5. **Balance snapshots**: Capture balance before/after to verify fee transfers\n6. **Timeouts**: Local tests 15-30s per action, devnet tests 120-240s (VRF)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Comprehensive File List**\n\n**Test Files** (spec.ts):\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/00-smoke.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/01-error-flow.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/02-cancel-flow.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/03-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/10-lord-smoke.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/11-lord-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/20-profile-transactions.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lord-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/deeplink.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/real/startup.spec.ts`\n\n**Fixture Files**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` (visual regression)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` (dual-player)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts` (devnet config)\n\n**Config Files**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` (visual)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` (local E2E)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts` (devnet E2E)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.real.config.ts` (staging/production)\n\n**Helper Files** (local):\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` (UI actions, 426 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/lord-page-objects.ts` (Lord UI, 308 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` (RPC assertions, 415 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` (keypairs, 87 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` (init, 197 lines)\n\n**Helper Files** (devnet, 3350 lines total):\n- `env.ts` (241 lines) — validate VITE_*, backend health\n- `wallets.ts` (20 lines) — keypairs\n- `on-chain-cleanup.ts` (218 lines) — clean stale matches\n- `cleanup-stale-rounds.ts` (209 lines) — clean stale Lord rounds\n- `retry.ts` (47 lines) — retry helper\n- `vrf-polling.ts` (246 lines) — poll Orao VRF\n- `mock-vrf-fallback.ts` (208 lines) — fallback mock if VRF times out\n- `lord-vrf-fallback.ts` (378 lines) — Lord-specific VRF fallback\n- `lord-on-chain-cleanup.ts` (254 lines) — clean Lord rounds\n- `tx-utils.ts` (96 lines) — sign transactions\n\n**Runner Scripts**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-local.sh` (151 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh` (170 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` (125 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-teardown.sh` (2443 bytes)\n\n**Mock Accounts** (for local VRF):\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-network-state.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-random-player-a.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-treasury.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-random-lord-round0.json`\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Summary: Complete Example Flow**\n\n**Local E2E test execution** (from `03-lifecycle.spec.ts`):\n\n```\n1. beforeAll():\n   - fundTestWallets() — airdrop 10 SOL to PLAYER_A & PLAYER_B\n   - initializeLocalnet() — create on-chain configs\n\n2. Test(\"coinflip full lifecycle\"):\n   - Player A navigates to /coinflip\n   - Player A creates match (0.005 SOL, heads)\n   - assertMatchCreated() — query RPC, verify PDA exists, phase=0\n   \n   - Player B navigates to /coinflip\n   - Player B waits for lobby card, joins match\n   \n   - Both wait for backend settlement (30s timeout)\n   - waitForResult() — poll UI for \"won\"/\"lost\"\n   \n   - assertMatchClosed() — verify PDA closed or phase=settled\n   - assertTreasuryFee() — verify fee deducted from treasury\n   \n   - Winner returns to lobby\n   - consoleA.assertClean(), consoleB.assertClean()\n```\n\n**Devnet E2E test execution** (similar but with VRF):\n- Longer timeouts (120-300s) for VRF fulfillment\n- Retries (2 attempts) in case of network issues\n- VRF polling fallback if real VRF times out\n- Clean stale matches before/after test"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9114e6b031a949f7 (use SendMessage with to: 'a9114e6b031a949f7' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72331\ntool_uses: 34\nduration_ms: 130617</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18302c5c-b9ec-4f75-9de3-1cbb537277bf","uuid":"81879ddf-1d38-45e6-b3db-404c63e6dba7","timestamp":"2026-03-25T14:10:16.834Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the E2E test setup in /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia. I need to understand:\n1. Where are E2E tests located? Check `e2e/local/` and `e2e/` directories\n2. What test framework is used (Playwright?)\n3. What does a typical local E2E test look like? Read a complete example\n4. What's the test infrastructure (config files, helpers, fixtures)?\n5. How are they run? (check package.json scripts for test:e2e)\n6. What pages/flows are currently tested?\n\nBe thorough - read full test files and config files.","agentId":"a9114e6b031a949f7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## E2E Test Setup Exploration Report\n\n### 1. **Test Framework & Location**\n\n**Framework**: Playwright 1.58.2 (test runner for browser automation)\n\n**Locations**:\n- Main E2E directory: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/`\n- Sub-directories:\n  - `local/` — Local validator tests (7 test files)\n  - `devnet/` — Devnet tests (5 test files)\n  - `visual/` — Visual regression tests (2 test files)\n  - `real/` — Real/staging tests (1 test file)\n  - `helpers/` — Shared helpers (profile assertions)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Test Directory Structure**\n\n```\ne2e/\n├── fixtures.ts                    # Visual regression fixture (animation freeze, deterministic seeding)\n├── local/\n│   ├── fixtures.ts               # Dual-player browser context fixture (playerA/playerB with injected keypairs)\n│   ├── 00-smoke.spec.ts          # App loads in real wallet mode\n│   ├── 01-error-flow.spec.ts     # Error cases: insufficient balance, join unavailable match, settle already-claimed\n│   ├── 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts    # Create → cancel → refund → recreate flow\n│   ├── 03-lifecycle.spec.ts      # Full lifecycle: create → join → resolve → claim\n│   ├── 10-lord-smoke.spec.ts     # Lord of RNGs page load smoke test\n│   ├── 11-lord-lifecycle.spec.ts # Lord full lifecycle: create → join → countdown → settle\n│   ├── 20-profile-transactions.spec.ts # Play match → verify transaction history\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── wallets.ts            # Deterministic keypairs (PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B)\n│       ├── localnet-setup.ts     # Initialize on-chain configs (not funded)\n│       ├── page-objects.ts       # UI action helpers (create, join, cancel, claim, etc.)\n│       ├── lord-page-objects.ts  # Lord-specific UI helpers\n│       └── on-chain.ts           # RPC assertions (match PDAs, treasury, fee verification)\n├── devnet/\n│   ├── fixtures.ts               # Devnet config fixture (validates env vars)\n│   ├── smoke.spec.ts             # Verify RPC health + deployed programs + wallet connection\n│   ├── lifecycle.spec.ts         # Full lifecycle on devnet with VRF + backend settlement\n│   ├── lord-lifecycle.spec.ts    # Lord lifecycle on devnet\n│   ├── closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts # Close Call lifecycle\n│   ├── deeplink.spec.ts          # Deep-link to match page by ID\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── wallets.ts            # Deterministic keypairs\n│       ├── env.ts                # Validate VITE_RPC_URL, program IDs, backend health\n│       ├── retry.ts              # Retry helper for async operations\n│       ├── on-chain-cleanup.ts   # Clean stale matches before/after tests\n│       ├── vrf-polling.ts        # Poll Orao VRF for fulfillment\n│       ├── mock-vrf-fallback.ts  # Fallback mock VRF if real VRF times out\n│       ├── tx-utils.ts           # Transaction signing utilities\n│       └── [lord-specific helpers]\n├── visual/\n│   ├── routes.spec.ts            # Visual snapshots of key routes (home, coinflip, etc.)\n│   └── states.spec.ts            # Visual snapshots of UI states (winning, losing, loading, etc.)\n└── real/\n    └── startup.spec.ts           # Smoke test for staging/production\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Test Framework Details**\n\n#### **Playwright Configuration Files**\n\n| File | Purpose | Target | Workers | Timeout | Web Server |\n|------|---------|--------|---------|---------|------------|\n| `playwright.config.ts` | Visual regression tests (snapshot-based) | `visual/**` | 1 | 60s | Vite on port 3000 (VITE_MOCK_MODE=true) |\n| `playwright.local.config.ts` | Local E2E tests (real wallet mode against local validator) | `local/**` | 1 | 60s | Vite on port 3002 (VITE_TEST_WALLET=true) |\n| `playwright.devnet.config.ts` | Devnet E2E tests (real programs with VRF) | `devnet/**` | 1 | 300s | Vite on port 3003 (inherits env vars) |\n| `playwright.real.config.ts` | Staging/production tests | `real/**` | 1 | Default | Manual (no web server) |\n\n**Key Configuration Details**:\n- **Parallel execution**: Disabled (workers: 1) — all tests run serially to avoid race conditions\n- **Retries**: 0 for local/visual, 2 for devnet (VRF can be slow)\n- **Screenshots**: Off for local/visual, only-on-failure for devnet, on for devnet video\n- **Trace**: Off for visual, retain-on-failure for local and devnet\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Fixtures**\n\n#### **Visual Regression Fixture** (`e2e/fixtures.ts`)\n\nExtends Playwright's `test` fixture with `stablePage`:\n- **Deterministic randomness**: Seeds Math.random() with Mulberry32 (seed 42)\n- **Crypto seeding**: Injects seeded crypto.getRandomValues() for deterministic Keypair.generate()\n- **Frozen Date**: Date.now() returns fixed timestamp (2026-01-01)\n- **Animation freezing**: Injects CSS to disable all transitions and animations\n- **SVG animation pausing**: Calls pauseAnimations() on all SVG elements\n- **Font readiness**: Waits for document.fonts.ready before proceeding\n- **Console error filtering**: Collects errors, filters noise (401, 403, 429, favicon, backend not running), fails if unhandled errors exist\n\n**Usage**:\n```ts\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\ntest(\"example\", async ({ stablePage }) => { ... });\n```\n\n#### **Local E2E Dual-Player Fixture** (`e2e/local/fixtures.ts`)\n\nExtends Playwright's `test` fixture with:\n- **playerAContext / playerBContext**: Isolated browser contexts for two players\n- **playerAPage / playerBPage**: Pages within each context\n- **playerAKeypair / playerBKeypair**: Deterministic keypairs (same as PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B from wallets.ts)\n- **connection**: Shared Solana RPC connection to local validator\n\n**Key mechanism**: Each context gets a `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` injected via `addInitScript()`, allowing TestWalletProvider to construct the correct Keypair at React render time.\n\n**Usage**:\n```ts\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\ntest(\"lifecycle\", async ({ playerAPage, playerBPage, connection }) => { ... });\n```\n\n#### **Devnet Fixture** (`e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts`)\n\nSimilar to local fixture but also exposes:\n- **devnetConfig**: Validated config object with RPC URL, program IDs, backend URL\n- **connection**: Connection to devnet RPC (not local)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Test Framework: What's Tested**\n\n#### **Local E2E Tests** (against local validator)\n\n1. **00-smoke.spec.ts**: App loads, header visible, wallet button visible, no console errors\n2. **01-error-flow.spec.ts**: \n   - Insufficient balance → creation rejected, no PDA created\n   - Join unavailable (cancelled) match → stays in lobby\n   - Settle already-claimed match → no stale settle buttons\n3. **02-cancel-flow.spec.ts**: \n   - Create → cancel → refund flow\n   - Balance validation (rent cost < 0.01 SOL)\n   - Re-creation after cancel\n4. **03-lifecycle.spec.ts** (Full lifecycle):\n   - Player A creates match (iron tier, heads)\n   - Player B joins match\n   - Backend settles (pre-loaded mock VRF in local validator)\n   - Match PDA closes, treasury fee deducted\n   - Winner can return to lobby\n   - Console error tracking\n5. **10-lord-smoke.spec.ts**: Lord of RNGs page loads\n6. **11-lord-lifecycle.spec.ts**:\n   - Create round → Player B joins (countdown starts) → backend settlement → verify treasury fee\n   - Uses withRetry() helper to poll round state\n7. **20-profile-transactions.spec.ts**:\n   - Play coinflip match → navigate to profile → click Transactions tab\n   - Verify transaction history (DEPOSIT, PAYOUT) displays in SOL\n   - Verify deep-links to `/coinflip/:matchId`\n\n#### **Devnet E2E Tests** (against deployed programs with real VRF)\n\n1. **smoke.spec.ts**:\n   - Verify devnet deployments reachable (RPC health, programs deployed)\n   - App loads against devnet\n   - Wallet connects with test keypair\n2. **lifecycle.spec.ts**:\n   - Create → join → backend settle (with VRF fulfillment) → verify\n   - Settlement timeout: 120s (VRF can take up to 180s)\n   - Uses withRetry() to poll round settlement\n3. **lord-lifecycle.spec.ts**: Similar to local, but with real VRF fulfillment\n4. **closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts**: Close Call (BTC prediction) game lifecycle\n5. **deeplink.spec.ts**: Navigate directly to `/coinflip/:matchId` and verify match loads\n\n#### **Visual Tests** (snapshot-based)\n\n1. **routes.spec.ts**: Snapshots of key routes (/, /coinflip, /lord-of-rngs, /profile)\n2. **states.spec.ts**: Snapshots of specific UI states (winning state, losing state, loading, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Helper Functions Overview**\n\n#### **Page Objects** (`local/helpers/page-objects.ts`, 426 lines)\n\n**Selectors** (CSS class-based):\n- Lobby: `.coinflip-lobby`, sidebar, main area\n- Tier selector: `.rng-tier-selector`, `.rng-tier-btn`, `.rng-tier-gem--{tier}`\n- Side selector: `.coinflip-side-btn--heads/tails`\n- Match cards: `.coinflip-match-card`, `.coinflip-match-card__join-btn`\n- Active match: `.coinflip-active-match`, `.coinflip-active-match__waiting`, `.coinflip-active-match__playing`\n- Result: `.coinflip-result__outcome`, `.coinflip-result__payout`\n- Error: `.rng-toast--error`\n\n**Key Actions**:\n- `waitForWalletConnected(page, timeout)` — wait for `.rng-wallet-button--connected`\n- `navigateToCoinflip(page)` — goto `/coinflip`, wait for main area\n- `enterWager(page, amountSol)` — fill `.rng-wager-input__input`\n- `selectSide(page, \"heads\"|\"tails\")` — click side button\n- `createMatch(page, amountSol, side)` — enter wager, select side, click \"Create Game\"\n- `joinMatch(page, matchIndex)` — click join button on nth match card\n- `cancelMatch(page)` — click \"Cancel Match\"\n- `claimOrSettle(page)` — click \"Claim Payout\" / \"Settle & Return\"\n- `backToLobby(page)` — click \"Back to Lobby\"\n- `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)` — wait for `.coinflip-sidebar__status` text\n- `waitForResult(page, timeout)` — poll UI for result (won/lost)\n- `assertLobbyEmpty(page)` — verify no match cards\n- `trackConsoleErrors(page)` — collect console errors (filters noise)\n\n#### **On-Chain Helpers** (`local/helpers/on-chain.ts`, 415 lines)\n\n**RPC Query Helpers**:\n- `getCoinflipProgram(connection)` — create Anchor program instance\n- `getMatchPda(creator, matchId)` — derive match PDA from [\"match\", creator, matchId]\n- `getConfigPda()` — derive coinflip config PDA\n- `snapshotBalance(connection, pubkey)` — get balance in lamports\n- `getBalanceLamports(connection, pubkey)` — same as snapshot\n\n**Assertion Helpers**:\n- `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, side)` — fetch match PDA, verify phase=0 (waiting), return { matchPda, creator, opponent (PublicKey.default), entryAmount }\n- `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)` — verify account no longer exists or phase=settled/refunded\n- `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)` — verify fee deducted: expected = Math.floor((entryAmount * 500) / 10000), actual = balanceAfter - balanceBefore, within ±10 lamports\n\n**Match Account Shape**:\n```ts\ninterface MatchAccount {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  server: PublicKey;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number; // 0=waiting, 1=locked, 2=settled, 3=refunded\n  commitment: Uint8Array;\n  algorithmVer: number;\n  targetSlot: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  resultHash: Uint8Array;\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  matchId: number[];\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n#### **Wallets** (`local/helpers/wallets.ts`, 87 lines)\n\n**Fixed Keypairs**:\n- `PLAYER_A` = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa))\n- `PLAYER_B` = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb))\n- Same keypairs used on every test run (deterministic)\n\n**Airdrop Helpers**:\n- `fundWallet(connection, pubkey, solAmount)` — request airdrop, confirm\n- `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl, solAmount)` — fund both players, verify balances, return { playerA, playerB, connection }\n\n#### **Localnet Setup** (`local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`, 197 lines)\n\n**Initialization**:\n- `initializeLocalnet()` — create platform config, coinflip config on local validator\n- `ensurePlayerProfiles()` — create player profile PDAs for testing profile transactions\n\n#### **Lord of RNGs Helpers** (`local/helpers/lord-page-objects.ts`, 308 lines)\n\n**Actions**:\n- `navigateToLord(page)` — goto `/lord-of-rngs`\n- `joinRound(page)` — click join button\n- `selectTier(page, tierIndex)` — select tier by index\n- `waitForSettlementUi(page, timeout)` — wait for settlement state in UI\n- Similar pattern to coinflip page objects\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Test Runner Scripts**\n\n#### **Local E2E Runner** (`scripts/run-e2e-local.sh`, 151 lines)\n\n**Full flow**:\n1. Start solana-test-validator with programs preloaded\n2. Check/start PostgreSQL\n3. Generate backend signer keypair\n4. Fund backend signer with 2 SOL\n5. Run backend migrations (DATABASE_URL, DB_SCHEMA, RPC_URL)\n6. Start fairness backend on port 3101 (or custom PORT)\n7. Wait for backend health check\n8. Run Playwright tests: `playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts`\n9. Cleanup on exit (kill backend, teardown validator)\n\n**Environment variables**:\n- `RPC_URL` (default: http://127.0.0.1:8899)\n- `PORT` (default: 3101)\n- `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (passed to web server)\n- `DATABASE_URL` (postgres:///postgres)\n- `DB_SCHEMA` (local_e2e)\n\n**Entry command**: `npm run test:e2e:local` or `pnpm test:e2e:local`\n\n#### **Devnet E2E Runner** (`scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh`, 170 lines)\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Source .env.local or .env.devnet for VITE_* vars\n2. Source backend .env for DATABASE_URL, SERVER_KEYPAIR, RPC_URL\n3. Validate required env vars (VITE_RPC_URL, VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID)\n4. Check if backend is already running (curl /health)\n5. If not: run migrations and start backend on port 3100\n6. Run Playwright tests: `playwright test --config playwright.devnet.config.ts`\n7. Cleanup on exit\n\n**Required env vars**:\n- `VITE_RPC_URL` — devnet RPC endpoint (default: dRPC)\n- `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`\n- `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID`\n- `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` (default: http://127.0.0.1:3100)\n\n**Entry command**: `npm run test:e2e:devnet` or `pnpm test:e2e:devnet`\n\n#### **Localnet Bootstrap** (`scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh`, 125 lines)\n\n**Starts solana-test-validator**:\n- Preloads 3 programs at fixed IDs: coinflip, platform, lordofrngs\n- Preloads Orao mock VRF accounts (network state, treasury, randomness for players)\n- Ledger dir: `.localnet-ledger`\n- Waits for RPC health, max 30s\n- Writes validator PID to `.localnet.pid`\n\n**Teardown** (`scripts/localnet-teardown.sh`):\n- Kills validator process by PID\n- Removes ledger directory\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Test Execution Order & Mode**\n\n**Local tests**:\n- **Serial**: 01-error-flow (serial block inside), 20-profile-transactions (serial block inside)\n- **Parallel-capable but run serially**: 00-smoke, 02-cancel, 03-lifecycle, 10-lord-smoke, 11-lord-lifecycle\n- **Execution**: Single worker, no parallelism across files\n\n**Devnet tests**:\n- **Serial**: All tests run serially (workers: 1)\n- **Retries**: 2 (to handle VRF timing variations)\n- **Long timeout**: 300s (VRF fulfillment can take up to 180s)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Page Objects & Selectors Summary**\n\n**Coinflip Page Structure**:\n- `.coinflip-page` (root container)\n  - `.coinflip-sidebar` (left: tier, side, summary, action button)\n  - `.coinflip-main` (right: lobby or active match)\n    - `.coinflip-lobby` (open matches list)\n      - `.coinflip-matches__list` → `.coinflip-match-card` (each match)\n    - `.coinflip-active-match` (in-progress or settled match)\n      - `.coinflip-active-match__waiting` (awaiting opponent)\n      - `.coinflip-active-match__playing` (countdown/revealing)\n      - `.coinflip-result__outcome` (won/lost)\n      - `.coinflip-result__payout` (amount)\n      - `.coinflip-active-match__post-claim` (after claiming)\n\n**Lord of RNGs Page Structure**:\n- Similar pattern: sidebar (tier select) + main (round list / active round)\n\n**Profile Page Structure**:\n- `.profile-page__header`\n- `button:has-text(\"Transactions\")` (tab selector)\n- `.profile-transactions__table` (transaction history)\n- `.profile-transactions__table tbody tr` (rows)\n- `.profile-transactions__match-link` (deep-link to /coinflip/:matchId)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Key Test Patterns**\n\n1. **Dual-player tests**: Use playerAPage + playerBPage from fixture, both auto-connect with test wallet\n2. **On-chain assertions**: After UI actions, query RPC to verify PDA state (phase, amount, winner)\n3. **Console error tracking**: Every test calls `trackConsoleErrors(page).assertClean()` at end\n4. **Retry with backoff**: Use `withRetry()` helper for eventual consistency (settlement can take time)\n5. **Balance snapshots**: Capture balance before/after to verify fee transfers\n6. **Timeouts**: Local tests 15-30s per action, devnet tests 120-240s (VRF)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Comprehensive File List**\n\n**Test Files** (spec.ts):\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/00-smoke.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/01-error-flow.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/02-cancel-flow.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/03-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/10-lord-smoke.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/11-lord-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/20-profile-transactions.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lord-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/deeplink.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/real/startup.spec.ts`\n\n**Fixture Files**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` (visual regression)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` (dual-player)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts` (devnet config)\n\n**Config Files**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` (visual)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` (local E2E)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts` (devnet E2E)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.real.config.ts` (staging/production)\n\n**Helper Files** (local):\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` (UI actions, 426 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/lord-page-objects.ts` (Lord UI, 308 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` (RPC assertions, 415 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` (keypairs, 87 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` (init, 197 lines)\n\n**Helper Files** (devnet, 3350 lines total):\n- `env.ts` (241 lines) — validate VITE_*, backend health\n- `wallets.ts` (20 lines) — keypairs\n- `on-chain-cleanup.ts` (218 lines) — clean stale matches\n- `cleanup-stale-rounds.ts` (209 lines) — clean stale Lord rounds\n- `retry.ts` (47 lines) — retry helper\n- `vrf-polling.ts` (246 lines) — poll Orao VRF\n- `mock-vrf-fallback.ts` (208 lines) — fallback mock if VRF times out\n- `lord-vrf-fallback.ts` (378 lines) — Lord-specific VRF fallback\n- `lord-on-chain-cleanup.ts` (254 lines) — clean Lord rounds\n- `tx-utils.ts` (96 lines) — sign transactions\n\n**Runner Scripts**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-local.sh` (151 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh` (170 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` (125 lines)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-teardown.sh` (2443 bytes)\n\n**Mock Accounts** (for local VRF):\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-network-state.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-random-player-a.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-treasury.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-random-lord-round0.json`\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Summary: Complete Example Flow**\n\n**Local E2E test execution** (from `03-lifecycle.spec.ts`):\n\n```\n1. beforeAll():\n   - fundTestWallets() — airdrop 10 SOL to PLAYER_A & PLAYER_B\n   - initializeLocalnet() — create on-chain configs\n\n2. Test(\"coinflip full lifecycle\"):\n   - Player A navigates to /coinflip\n   - Player A creates match (0.005 SOL, heads)\n   - assertMatchCreated() — query RPC, verify PDA exists, phase=0\n   \n   - Player B navigates to /coinflip\n   - Player B waits for lobby card, joins match\n   \n   - Both wait for backend settlement (30s timeout)\n   - waitForResult() — poll UI for \"won\"/\"lost\"\n   \n   - assertMatchClosed() — verify PDA closed or phase=settled\n   - assertTreasuryFee() — verify fee deducted from treasury\n   \n   - Winner returns to lobby\n   - consoleA.assertClean(), consoleB.assertClean()\n```\n\n**Devnet E2E test execution** (similar but with VRF):\n- Longer timeouts (120-300s) for VRF fulfillment\n- Retries (2 attempts) in case of network issues\n- VRF polling fallback if real VRF times out\n- Clean stale matches before/after test"}],"totalDurationMs":130617,"totalTokens":72331,"totalToolUseCount":34,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":466,"cache_read_input_tokens":64429,"output_tokens":7436,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":466},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
