{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GPhn8ZiDPeagp97Z8jNsVS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me also check how the auth flow works in the local E2E - specifically, does the wallet auto-connect and auto-authenticate against the local backend? Let me check the profile-transactions test, which goes to `/profile` and uses auth APIs.\n\nActually from the profile-transactions test, I can see:\n```typescript\nconst authDone = playerAPage.waitForResponse(\n  (r) => r.url().includes(\"/auth/\") && r.status() < 400,\n  { timeout: 15_000 },\n);\nawait playerAPage.goto(\"/profile\");\n\n\nawait authDone;\n```\n\nThis confirms the app auto-authenticates via challenge-response when navigating to protected pages. I can apply the same pattern to the referral tests.\n\nFor the referral system E2E tests, I should cover: capturing the referral link code when navigating to `/r/:code` and verifying it's stored in localStorage, rendering the `/referrals` page with proper authentication, and setting the referral code through the appropriate flow.\n\nThe test structure would have Player A set a referral code on the referrals page, Player B visit the referral link which stores the code locally and redirects home, then after wallet connection and authentication the referral gets auto-applied through a hook. Finally, Player A's referrals page should display the referred player count and Player B's profile should show who referred them.\n\nThe `useReferralApply` hook in `App.tsx` checks for authentication, access token, wallet address, and a stored referral code before calling the apply endpoint. So the flow is: Player B lands on the referral link, the code gets saved to localStorage and they're redirected home, then once the wallet connects and authenticates, the hook automatically applies the referral. The timing of the redirect might be tight though.\n\nSetting up the test...\n\nI'm setting up the first part of the test where Player A navigates to the referrals page, waits for authentication to complete, and then enters a custom referral code into the form.\n\nNow I'm filling in the referral code input field with \"e2e-test-ref\", clicking the button to set it, and then verifying that the generated URL contains the code we just set. After that, I'm moving on to the second part of the test where Player B will visit the referral link to check if it redirects properly.\n\nSetting up Player B's referral link visit...\n\nNow I'm navigating to the profile settings page and waiting for the auth response to complete, then clicking into the Settings tab to verify that the referral section displays Player A's wallet address as the referrer.\n\nThen Player A checks their referrals page to confirm the stats show exactly 1 referred player.\n\nActually, I'm realizing there are some issues with how I'm handling the redirect flow. The `ReferralCapture` component uses client-side navigation, so when Player B visits `/r/e2e-test-ref`, the page loads and stores the code in localStorage before redirecting to `/`. But `waitUntil: \"domcontentloaded\"` might fire before that redirect completes. And then when the page lands on `/`, the auth flow kicks in automatically, so I need to make sure I'm properly waiting for both the auth response and the apply response to finish. Let me reconsider how Player B's flow should work—starting with the redirect to the referral code, then handling what happens when the page navigates to the home route. I need to be careful about the timing here—`goto()` might resolve before the React redirect completes, so using `waitForURL` to confirm the navigation to `/` is the safer approach. In a single-page app with React Router, the initial `goto()` triggers a full page load where the server returns the same HTML, and then React Router handles the client-side routing, so the URL change should be detectable. In test mode, the wallet auto-connects immediately, then the auth flow runs (challenge-response with the backend), and finally `useReferralApply` fires to read localStorage and call the apply endpoint. I need to set up a response listener for the `/referral/apply` POST before navigating, so I can wait for it to confirm the apply succeeded.\n\nSetting up response listener...\n\nThe key thing is that Player A needs to set the referral code first before Player B visits the link, since the code won't exist otherwise. So the test sequence has to be: Player A creates \"e2e-test-ref\", then Player B navigates to that referral link and the auto-apply happens.\n\nI'm also noticing from the profile-transactions test that navigating to a new page with `goto` triggers a full page reload and re-authentication, which means I need to set up the response listener before the navigation happens to catch the auth flow.\n\nFor the test scope, I should focus on what the checklist actually requires. I'm realizing that testing the full earnings flow from game settlement would be too complex for a local E2E test since it requires playing an actual match and waiting for settlement. Instead, I'll focus the test on the referral management flows I can control: setting a code, applying it, and verifying the page renders correctly with the right sections and empty states.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2103,"cache_read_input_tokens":66316,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2103},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18302c5c-b9ec-4f75-9de3-1cbb537277bf","uuid":"e1512d25-b442-4f3b-9906-dbf3bcba8690"}
